HSINKING newspaper Reporter, Deng Qi, Sha Xueliang, photojournalist, editor of Tao Ran Zheng Xinqia, Zhang Chang, proofreader, Wu Xingfa

Ye Qing stood by the window, unable to hear the traffic.

Living in Wuhan for 40 years, he felt for the first time that the city was frozen, like a sudden heavy snow, completely buried here, extremely quiet.

By February 23, Ye Qing, deputy director of the Statistics Bureau of Hubei Province, had written the diary of the epidemic area, part 30.

Back more than 30 days ago, Ye Qing felt the "real tension" among Wuhan residents. The newly established epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters issued five announcements in the early morning and late at night, announcing the closure of the Han corridor, Wuhan "closed city. ".

The outbreak of new crown pneumonia, which began in late 2019, has thrown Wuhan, a 3,000-year-old central city of more than 11 million people, into a challenge never seen before in the history of New China's urban governance.

In the meantime, Wuhan Fire Line changes the commander in chief, promotes the accountability parallel. A series of prevention and control measures have been implemented, and all forces throughout the country are rushing to help. On February 20, Ding Xiangyang, Deputy secretary-general of the State Council and a member of the Central Steering Group, said at a press conference that overall, the epidemic in Hubei Province and Wuhan has slowed down from its previous explosive growth.

"If prevention and control measures are put in place, the downward trend will not change, starting from the previous peak and gradually descending, " the central guidance team said in its latest assessment of the Hubei and Wuhan Epidemics.

At 4:35 pm on 23 January, passengers queued up at a manual counter at Wuhan Tianhe International Airport. From 10:00 on the same day, Wuhan bus subway suspended operation, the airport railway station from the Han Channel was temporarily closed. Photographer / Beijing News Reporter, Zheng Xinqia

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
━━━━━

The unprecedented order to seal off the city

"It looks like this time is no joke, " said Ye Qing, deputy director of the Statistics Bureau of Hubei Province, who has lived in Wuhan for 40 years.

When Ye Qing woke up at 6:30 a.m. , he reposted the news on his microblog. The man who has repeatedly called for bus reform, dubbed "China's most individualistic official" , really feels the nerves of Wuhan's citizens.

At 2:00 a.m. that day, the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and control headquarters issued the first announcement, announcing that from 10:00 on January 23, the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services would be suspended; there was no special reason, people are not allowed to leave Wuhan. Airport and railway stations are temporarily closed.

Wuhan residents were not surprised. News of the outbreak has been pouring in for days. On the night of January 20, Zhong Nanshan identified "human-to-human" cases of NCP; on January 22,69 new cases were reported in Hubei, including 62 in Wuhan and 8 deaths.

"closed city" , is the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters after the establishment, issued the first notice. Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang on this interpretation, is to cut off the source of infection, to prevent the spread of the epidemic to the country.

Among the six central provinces, Wuhan is the only sub-province-level division, an important inland water, land and air transport hub. The high-speed rail network covers more than half of China and is known as the "thoroughfare of the nine provinces" . Wuhan is also the aviation hub in central China, with more than 50 international routes, is the only city in central China with direct flights to five continents.

Nearly 300,000 people left the city by rail the day before the city was closed, according to figures released by the Wuhan Bureau of the Chinese Railway. Among them, nearly 160,000 passengers were sent a block away from the south China Seafood Market in Hankou Railway Station, where the virus is believed to have originated.

According to incomplete statistics, on January 23 from 0:00-10:00, from Wuhan can reach large and medium-sized cities of the train at least 251, along Wuhan "meter"-shaped rail network, bound for all parts of the country.

That day early in the morning to late at night, the headquarters of five consecutive circular issued.

Wuhan has ample reserves and smooth supply of commodities, food and medical and protective supplies, the second circular said. Please don't panic, don't hoard. In the announcement on the 3rd, Wuhan launched a 24-hour telephone service to receive donations of medical consumables, protective supplies and other materials from all walks of life to combat the epidemic. The donation details are posted on circular four. The notice announced on the 5th: Starting from 12:00 on January 24, Wuhan city-wide net about taxi stop operation, Parade Taxi odd-even number.

The danger of light analysis of the situation at home, some at a loss.

The wife needs to take medicine regularly, where to buy? Graduate School Children at home, a family of three daily consumption of food many, how to protect?

Wei Guang undertakes the task of family procurement on weekdays. Before the closing, he went to the supermarket every other day, which was terribly crowded. On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, he dug up some dried sweet potato flour from his home and cooked some for the family of three.

"closed city" , the third and sixth day of Weiguang Big Walk to the supermarket to buy food, and then never out of the district. He tried to get out-of-town friends to express him some put ingredients, such as carrots, potatoes, due to traffic control, was not successful.

Members of the Hubei Medical team pose for a photo before boarding a plane at Beijing Capital International Airport on Jan. 27. Photo by Tao ran, Beijing News

A hospital that can't be stopped

"It's all stopped, " Ye Qing said. A City can be loud and quiet. In this special period, only stop, can tide over the difficulties.

But the hospital won't stop.

Fever clinics are available in 61 health-care facilities in Wuhan and fever clinics are available in all community health service centres for screening and differential diagnosis of fever patients.

As fever patients proliferate, a bed is hard to find, and many fever clinics are overloaded. Many fever patients crowded into the hospital overnight queue, become a potential source of infection.

Infectious Diseases need to be treated in special hospitals. Previously, there were only two special infectious disease hospitals in Wuhan, Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital and Wuhan Lung Hospital, with more than 900 beds.

In order to Split Second patients, at the end of January, 24 general hospitals were requisitioned in three batches in Wuhan on the basis of the first two designated hospitals and 61 fever clinics, with reference to the basic requirements of the Infectious Disease Prevention and treatment institutions, temporarily converted into a hospital for patients with fever.

The lack of beds, combined with the initial lack of kits and the slow pace of testing, meant many patients died before they could be diagnosed.

On January 24th and 25th, Wuhan decided to follow the model of Beijing's Xiaotangshan Hospital and build Wuhan's Huoshenshan and Raytheon hospitals to step up efforts to treat patients. Together, the two hospitals provide about 2,600 beds.

On January 27, the then Wuhan Party secretary, Ma Guoqiang, gave a set of data at a press conference: Since the outbreak of the epidemic, the number of fever outpatient clinics in Wuhan has increased day by day. In previous years, this season, the number of fever outpatient clinics in the city was about 3,000 per day, in the past few days, there have been more than 15,000 visits to fever clinics during peak hours, and fever clinics are indeed operating at an overload with a large number of people queuing up in the face of an instantaneous increase in attendance.

The surge in patients has made medical supplies even more scarce.

In a recent interview with the Beijing News, Bryan Chan, deputy director of the Wuhan First Hospital, said that supplies were the biggest headache at the beginning of the New Year. "When I came out of the hospital the other night, I felt very anxious, very helpless and very sorry for the medical staff. They work here ten hours a day and they can't go home. I can't even guarantee the safety of my own employees as a manager. What am I supposed to tell them?"

On New Year's Eve, Bryan Chan ate his lunch box and discussed how many masks, how many suits, and how many days he had left. Every day he kept calling the headquarters, from various channels of society to get protective clothing, masks, but also launched charity fund-raising.

The shortage of protective materials is a dilemma faced by hospitals in Wuhan. Some medical staff said that put on the protective clothing dare not take off, take off may not. Once you put it on, it means you won't be able to breathe in your suit until the end of the day.

Health care workers are also at increased risk of infection. In the early morning of January 21, Wuhan Health Commission first reported, the city's 15 medical staff confirmed, there is another suspected case. As at 2400 hours on 11 February, 1,102 confirmed cases had been reported in Wuhan and several medical staff had died in the line of duty.

Ma Guoqiang has talked about the shortage of medical staff, said masks because of the Spring Festival shutdown and other reasons, resulting in periods of tension. He cited protective clothing as one of the most critical resources, and he believed that as production rates increased and sourcing expanded, access would expand.

Too late to wait for government deployment, many hospitals in the online charity fund-raising.

With the support of all over Hubei, a large number of social goods poured in, the Red Cross involved in the vortex of public opinion. Public questions, Hubei and Wuhan Red Cross material distribution unfair, inefficient distribution, the latter also involved in the "monopoly Shandong donated Wuhan Vegetables, " the collection of service fees and so on.

Ma Guoqiang told CCTV in an interview on January 31 that he felt guilty, guilty and self-reproach during this period. "I have been thinking that if I had decided earlier to take such drastic measures as we have now, the results would have been better, the impact on all parts of the country would have been smaller, and the Party Central Committee and the State Council would have been less worried. "

On February 8, Wuhan Union Hospital, Beijing Chaoyang Hospital, assisted the Wuhan Medical Team and Colleagues Far Away in Beijing for medical consultation. Photo by Tao ran, Beijing News

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"The play has changed. "

February 13, Hubei Province Health Commission data showed that due to statistical changes, February 12,14,840 new cases of coronary pneumonia in Hubei Province, including 13,332 cases of clinical diagnosis, of which 13,436 new cases in Wuhan, the first new case of a single day more than 10,000.

On this day, Hubei"change a handsome".

Ying Yong became a member, member and secretary of the Hubei Provincial Committee; Wang Zhonglin served as a member, member and secretary of the Hubei Provincial Committee and the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee. Both Ying Yong and Wang have years of experience in the political and legal systems, according to their public records.

A few days earlier, Wang Hesheng, deputy director of the National Health Commission, "parachuted" to Hubei to become a member of the Standing Committee of the provincial committee, and later concurrently served as secretary of the Leading Party Group and director of the Hubei Provincial Health Commission. Wang Hesheng was trained as a medical student and worked in Tianjin Health System for many years. He has rich experience and currently ranks first among the four deputy directors of the National Health Commission.

"At last, those who know medicine have arrived, " Ye Qing said as he read the news that "Wang He is qualified to serve on the Standing Committee of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee. ".

In less than a week, the leadership of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee welcomed three "New People" from outside the province to adjust Hubei and Wuhan, which are the top priority in epidemic prevention and control, and the provincial health and health committees, which are specifically responsible for epidemic prevention and control in Hubei Province.

After the new leadership took office, Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and control of the pace significantly accelerated.

The newly appointed party secretary of Hubei Province, Ying Yong, presided over the symposium at the first time, proposing to seize the important window period, grasp the two key links of treatment and obstruction. "Cure" "block" of the four-character formulation, some media evaluation as "beat the snake finally hit seven inches.

New Secretary of Wuhan Municipal Party Committee Wang Zhonglin in hospitals, communities, supermarkets and other places research, found that some small-scale prevention and control in the form of some large-scale network-based investigation. He announced the launch of a three-day centralized network clearance clearance clearance. "This can not wait any longer! "

Before this, Wuhan is checked because"Mesh is too big"public opinion is questioned. Ma Guoqiang a week ago released the "household survey percentage of 98.6% " of the statistics, some Wuhan Netizen said, so far no one on their own survey. Many "hospital admission difficult" help posts, constantly posted on Weibo and other social media.

The new official takes office Wang Zhonglin, has burned the big investigation "the fire" . He said, only to find people, to find people, to implement the "should be collected. ". Do not know the bottom number, this battle"pestilence"very difficult to win. "Wuhan is the place for decisive battle. We should concentrate our efforts on the war of annihilation, not on the protracted war of slackness and slackness. "

Wang Zhonglin proposed, the request takes the community as the foundation, uses the manpower and the big data union, thoroughly clears the bottom "four categories of personnel" . Adhere to the "do not leak a door, do not leak a person. ".

During the three-day investigation, Wang Zhonglin once again secretly visited many communities. On February 18, he went to the Baibu Pavilion, where he once had a "feast of ten thousand families" . On Feb. 19, he deployed on the spot: The districts made a commitment to make sure there were no confirmed or suspected patients at home. "We can't take it lightly. People's lives are at stake. If there's another case, we'll take it up with the District Party secretary and the district chief. "

Three days of dragnet-style large survey to hand in the answer sheet. According to the Feb. 23 report, the Wuhan Police assisted in the investigation, transportation and treatment of 3,502"four categories of people" , including 559 confirmed patients, 820 suspected patients, 283 fever patients, and 1,840 close contacts.

A series of thunder means, let Wuhan people see hope.

"I think this can be said to be the Wuhan model, " Ye Qing said, adding that after Wang arrived in Wuhan, the city's dragnet-style search was very effective. If it had been done earlier, the closure measures would probably be basically over by now.

More citizens saw Wuhan in various aspects of epidemic prevention and control as "Wuhan's fighting style changed. "

Medics help each other put on protective clothing at Wuhan Union Hospital on Feb. 2. Photo by Tao ran, Beijing News

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Full-scale escalation of containment

Before this, Wuhan Prevention and control of the epidemic strategy, including the city's prevention and control measures, medical treatment capacity, "four categories of people" screening and admission, and so on, has been criticized several times.

Officials from the State Health Commission's Medical Administration and Hospital Authority have said that the outbreak in Wuhan has lasted for a long time, and many community cases have not been treated in time because prevention and control measures were not put in place in time. The average time from onset to hospitalization was 9.84 days for severe cases. The 10 days missed the best opportunity and the waiting period changed from mild to severe cases.

Chen Yixin, secretary general of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission and deputy head of the Central Steering Group, said Wuhan had not yet fully figured out the number of infected people in the epidemic prevention and control, nor did it have a more accurate estimate of the scale of the spread.

For patients in transit, especially in the transit of critically ill patients, Wuhan also has the problems of disorganization and disorder, which leads to serious dissatisfaction among the masses. Department heads from Wuchang District, Kong Hon, Hubei and Wuhan Health Committees were interviewed by the Central Guidance Team.

Despite the announcement on January 23 that the city would be closed, several Wuhan residents said that for more than 20 days, people were still lining up to shop in the streets and supermarkets.

After Ying Yong, Hubei's new secretary, listed "isolation" as a key link alongside "treatment, " Wuhan announced stricter management of gated communities. Ye Qing saw that the Wuhan community, except for certain people, are prohibited from entering or leaving, everyone can not walk in the community, day by day more strict. Originally, they can go to the supermarket shopping, February 15, only through e-commerce distribution, after the items sent downstairs to pick up.

Wang Zhonglin also proposed that, wuhan is to achieve "five hundred percent" -- "100 percent collection for confirmed patients, 100 percent nucleic acid testing for suspected patients, 100 percent testing for Febrile patients, 100 percent isolation for close contacts, 100 percent 24-hour closed management for small communities and villages. " We will resolutely curb the spread of the epidemic.

Wuhan also through promotion and accountability, constantly adjust the "generals" team.

As of February 21, Wuhan had promoted 20 cadres and 34 party members to the front line, and the discipline inspection and supervision organs had investigated and dealt with 385 problems, handled 620 people in terms of accountability, 6 cadres at the bureau level and 127 at the department level.

Residents of Wuhan are clearly feeling the change.

Jinna, a native of Wuhan, said the outbreak had caught people off guard, like a sudden outbreak of war in a peaceful era. Early information is not transparent, people do not give attention to the epidemic. Now that a series of big moves has been launched, people feel more at ease.

Her classmate, Liu Xia, also noted that the government's policies have become more detailed and more people's livelihood, and has gradually introduced some convenient policies for residents, such as the addition of designated pharmacies to facilitate the purchase of medicines for patients with severe chronic diseases. Wuhan Health Commission announced some of the medical institutions for non-new coronary pneumonia patients to meet the medical needs of chronic severe patients, pregnant women, children and other medical needs.

A citizen became the Fire Mountain Hospital site of the ferry volunteers, a day in the construction site and parking point to and fro more than 100 times, send construction workers back to the site. Photo by Tao ran, Beijing News

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On New Year's Eve (January 24) , hundreds of people in the Wuhan Hotel Industry spontaneously formed the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance to provide free and convenient accommodation for first-line medical staff. Volunteers deliver sterile water to the Union hotel. Photo courtesy of the respondents

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Support from all sides

In the crisis of the epidemic, the people are also saving themselves.

Jinna flew from Wuhan to Seoul, South Korea, years ago. Affected by the epidemic, changed 5 tickets, February 4, smoothly from Seoul to Zhuhai temporary stay.

Unable to return to Wuhan, became her miss.

See Wuhan "closed city" , confirmed the number of rising day by day, Jinna is very worried, want to do something to help his hometown. Later, she joined a rescue mission organized by her classmates at the Wuhan University to help connect private and Hubei hospitals with information about supplies. The group has helped people from all over the country donate 4,000 goggles, more than 510,000 pairs of medical gloves and 8,000 KN95 masks to dozens of medical institutions in Hubei.

"everyone back home is in a position to help as many people as possible, " Jinna said.

The spontaneous rescue behavior of the folk emerged in various fields. In order to provide free and convenient accommodation for the medical staff who are fighting against the epidemic, hundreds of people in the Wuhan Hotel Industry spontaneously formed the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance on New Year's Eve (January 24) . As of 2100 hours on 30 January, the alliance had provided more than 40,000 overnight accommodations for a total of 6,056 health care workers.

The idea was simple, said Xiao Yaxing, a hotel owner and the alliance's first founder. Health care workers work too hard, many live too far away, transport is difficult, general hotels may be afraid to let them stay, and many hotels are closed again. My hotel was empty, so I thought I'd put it up for the paramedics.

"We are a collective that deserves to be remembered. " Xiao yaxing believes that by joining the alliance, he is providing love.

Li Chao, the CO founder, said the alliance was a group of people who had done something to their conscience.

Liu Xia, a bed-and-breakfast owner, has also joined the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support League. As of 22 February, bed-and-breakfast accommodation had provided more than 600 overnight stays for 51 medical staff.

And a volunteer convoy of ordinary citizens. They wear masks, carry disinfectant, and use a taxi-hailing platform to shuttle frontline medical staff to and from work free of charge.

Under the epidemic situation, it became difficult to buy medicine, many Wuhan residents spontaneously joined the action of giving medicine to patients free of charge. Hospitals were short-staffed, and many sanitation workers were busy at designated and shelter hospitals in Wuhan.

There are people, become the Vulcan Mountain ferry volunteers, a day in the construction site and parking between more than a hundred times, send the construction workers back to the site.

More people are starting to pay attention to the "psychological" issues behind the epidemic.

During the outbreak, a number of psychological counseling institutions, associations of psychological counselors, and college psychology schools in Wuhan, Jiangsu, Guizhou, Henan, Beijing, Shanghai and other places have set up hotlines to provide psychological assistance to Wuhan and other parts of the country.

Crisis isn't worried about grocery shopping anymore. Community to the volunteers, every day, the residents of the procurement needs to Wechat Group, volunteers on behalf of the procurement, and then unified to the community, equivalent to group purchase.

Four confirmed patients were discharged from Wuhan Union Hospital on February 13, with one dancing. Photo by Tao ran, Beijing News

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I'm just looking forward to another bowl of hot and dry noodles

Extraordinary rule has had a positive effect.

On February 20, Ding Xiangyang, Deputy secretary-general of the State Council and a member of the Central Steering Group, said at a press conference at the New China office in Wuhan that overall, the outbreaks in Hubei Province and Wuhan had slowed from their previous explosive growth. "If prevention and control measures are put in place, the downward trend will not change, starting from the previous peak gradually downward. "

The number of confirmed cases in Wuhan, other cities in Hubei and other provinces across the country has shown a downward trend, according to the National Health Commission on Feb. 22. Among them, 36,680 cases were recorded in Wuhan on February 21, down from a peak of 38,020 on February 18.

Fang Fang, a writer in Wuhan, said that with the arrival of the new leaders, "Hubei's approach to fighting the epidemic has changed from its previous slowness and imbecility. "

Back to work, home, Wuhan residents began to have a new hope.

As a bed-and-breakfast operator, Liu Xia's state of mind is delayed time to return to work again and again make very anxious. He was ready to resume work on February 20, intended to resume work on a bank loan to ease the pressure of fund flow, unexpectedly, and postponed.

Recently, Liu Xia, along with several other hotels, was requisitioned by the government for a fee to receive some medical personnel from other places to support Wuhan, slightly easing the operating pressure. He also plans to talk to landlords and employees about cutting rents, wages and costs. He began to give staff training, so that everyone ready to resume work, and exchange after the resumption of health, disinfection process. He estimated that in March, Wuhan may periodically resume some social activities, such as transportation and some necessary enterprises and units. "Our small and medium-sized enterprises can not stand it, and the human spirit has reached a critical point. "

Ye Qing is concerned about the economic impact of the outbreak, especially among the less well off. He suggested that the government provide volunteer positions and subsidies to tide them over. "after this epidemic, we have to reflect: In addition to economic development, but also to protect the environment, protect health. Our vice-governor in charge of public health and the director of the Health Construction Commission should study and understand medicine. To establish a comprehensive emergency response system, in the north of Guangzhou, Wuhan, Chengdu and other key nodes in the deployment of public health and safety emergency base, can quickly deal with the surrounding epidemic. In addition, there should be a reserve of emergency resources, including masks, goggles, etc. ."

Jinna sees experts saying new coronaviruses could co exist with humans for a long time to come. She recalled a passage from the plague: Plague Bacilli never completely die or disappear; they can lie dormant in furniture or clothing for decades. Waiting for a sign of doom or human misfortune, when the plague will once again rouse its rats and send them to a happy city to sow death.

"humanity should reflect, " Jinna said.

The situation is still serious, and Jinna will not be able to return to Wuhan anytime soon. The government is still expanding the shelter hospital, and the number of confirmed cases is still high. But JINNA saw the light. She looked forward to the early resolution of the epidemic, wondering if she could return to Wuhan in May.

The first thing she planned to do when she returned to Wuhan was to get together with her relatives and friends and hug them. And have another bowl of hot and dry noodles.

(Wei Guang, Liu Xia and Jinna are all pseudonyms)
